file io text and bin mode
-----------------------------------------
Text files
    Config → .txt, .ini
    Logs → .log
    Data → .csv, .json
    Docs → .md
    Scripts → .sh, .py

Binary files
    Game saves → .sav, .bin
    Database → .db
    Cache → .cache, .dat
    Media → .png, .mp3, .mp4
    System → .exe, .o, .so

Rule:
    Readable = text | ⚙️ Fast/compact = binary

-------------------------------------------
One-line takeaway
    C++ gives power, not convenience.
    Parsers are built, not gifted.
-------------------------------------------
ini/cfg file: motive is same, style is different 

INI = organized & readable
CFG = simple & efficient

Why C++ devs like CFG
    Easier to parse
    Faster
    Less syntax rules
    Customizable
----------------------------------------------